  "title": "OPERATIONS LIAISON ASSISTANT",
  "description": "<p>1) Model, motivate and communicate regularly to all site staff on the mission, vision, and core values</p>\n<p>2) Prepare, organize, collate and submit all required operational and HR documentation to achieve compliance guidelines and deadlines</p>\n<p>3) Forecast, plan, recruit and deploy manpower duties and schedules to meet the site contractual requirements</p>\n<p>4) Guide, coach, and inspect daily and ad-hoc cleaning jobs and tasks are performed according to clients expectations and SOPs guidelines</p>\n<p>5) Conduct and monitor effective OJT training to all new operations staff based on the training blueprint standards to achieve operational excellence and skillsets</p>\n<p>6) Attend to all feedbacks or complaints from clients and take immediate measures to solve the issues and prevent future recurrence</p>\n<p>7) To place an order, replenish, monitor, and track cleaning material stock and equipment to achieve minimum wastage</p>\n<p>8) Conduct and upkeep proper record of Client's Meeting. Toolbox meeting staff safety Induction and all relevant Workplace Safety &amp; Health documentation</p>",
